NAME: helloworld

AUTHOR:

DESCRIPTION:

Describe your application here.

HelloWorld is built on the Cement CLI Application Framework.


USAGE:

    $ helloworld --help
    
    
PLUGIN DEVELOPMENT:

HelloWorld supports external plugins via the Cement Framework.  To quick
start a new plugin for helloworld you can use the paster utility.

Setup a virtual environment for development:
    
    $ virtualenv --no-site-package /path/to/env
    
    $ source /path/to/env/bin/activate
    
    
Install HelloWorld:
    
    $ cd /path/to/HelloWorld
    
    $ python setup.py develop
    

Create and install the plugin:

    $ mkdir plugins
    
    $ cd plugins
    
    $ paster cement-plugin helloworld myplugin
    
    $ cd helloworld-plugins-myplugin
    
    $ python setup.py develop
    
    
Once your plugin is installed, you can add the plugin to the enabled_plugins
setting in /etc/helloworld/helloworld.conf (or the path to the config).  
Additionally, the plugin configurations can be set in 
/etc/helloworld/plugins.d/myplugin.conf. You should then see some example 
commands/options show up with:

    $ helloworld --help
    
    
Then, code away!
